==English==
===Noun===
'''Bible-basher''' (''plural'' '''Bible-bashers''')
# {{UK}} (''perjorative'') A [[fundamentalist]] [[Christian]] [[preacher]], who is seen to take every opportunity to talk about Christianity and convert those around them, especially against the other peoples' wills.
#: ''I don't ever go to my local church any more, it's become filled with stupid, [[fuddy-duddy]] '''bible bashers'''...''
# {{rfv-sense}} {{US}} A person who tries to find fault with the [[Bible]], [[Christianity]] or Christian teaching.

====Synonyms====
*[[Bible thumper]] (''US'')
*[[God botherer]] (''UK'')

====Antonyms====
*'''Bible basher''' (''US'')